{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"ferric-jet-scorpion","description":"## Summary\nThe completion-verification close gate's deterministic referencing-commit precondition (`src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py`, `_completion_precheck` / `_referencing_commit_exists`) evaluates a ticket in isolation: it blocks the close of any ticket that records `file_impact` unless a commit references **that ticket's own id** via a `rebar-ticket:` trailer. A parent (epic/story) whose code is delivered by its children's commits therefore cannot close — even though every child landed a referencing commit and closed signed — forcing a `--force-close` that leaves the parent unsigned.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n- [ ] Create an epic with `file_impact` set (a planning hint) and decompose it into children.\n- [ ] Implement each child; each commit carries a `rebar-ticket: <child>` trailer (not the epic's id). Close each child (they close signed).\n- [ ] `rebar transition <epic> in_progress closed`.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- **Expected:** The precondition credits the parent's entire descendant subtree — if the epic (or any descendant) has a referencing commit, the \"work landed\" precondition passes, the completion verifier runs on the epic's own criteria, and the epic can close **signed**.\n- **Actual:** `Error: cannot close <epic>: it records file_impact (a code change) but no commit references it.` The gate never looks at descendant commits, so the only way to close is `--force-close` (unsigned).\n\n## Design\nEvaluate the referencing-commit precondition over the ticket **and its entire descendant subtree** (transitive — an epic is satisfied by grandchild task commits). Build the accepted-id set = `{ticket}` ∪ all descendants (via `rebar._engine_support.descendants.list_descendants`), resolve each, and pass the precondition if **any** commit trailer resolves into that set. `_referencing_commit_exists` takes a set of resolved ids and returns True on the first match.\n\nSoundness: the open-children guard runs first, so a parent only reaches this precondition once all children are closed, and each child already passed this exact referencing-commit check at its own close — so crediting descendants cannot admit unlanded work. Stays deterministic (no LLM).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py`: the referencing-commit precondition passes when a `rebar-ticket:` trailer references the ticket **or any of its descendants** (transitive subtree via `list_descendants`); a ticket with `file_impact` and no referencing commit anywhere in its subtree still fails closed.\n- [ ] `_referencing_commit_exists` accepts a set of accepted resolved ids and returns True on the first commit whose extracted+resolved ref is in the set (behavior for the single-id case is unchanged).\n- [ ] The block message names the subtree (e.g. \"no commit references it (nor any of its descendants)\").\n- [ ] A leaf ticket (no descendants) with `file_impact` and its own referencing commit still closes; a leaf with `file_impact` and no referencing commit still fails closed (no regression).\n- [ ] Tests cover: parent with file_impact + a grandchild referencing commit → precondition passes; parent with file_impact + no subtree commit → fails closed; leaf unchanged (both directions).","id":"1edf-2261-a092-43e5","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"close gate: credit descendant commits when checking a parent's referencing-commit precondition"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783813621342227001,"uuid":"9abe1747-2da3-436e-906d-befba14db4dc"}